    • Method Detail

      • compare

        public int compare​(Stock thisRef,
                   Stock anotherStock)
        The compare method returns an int for the total order of the two Stocks. Total order is defined as < 0 if the thisRef purchase price is less than the anotherStock purchase price, equal to 0 if they are the same and > 0 if thisRef purchase price is greater than anotherStock purchase price.
        Specified by:
        compare in interface Comparator<Stock>
        Parameters:
        thisRef - Representing the first Stock value passed in
        anotherStock - Representing the second Stock value passed in
        Returns:
        int Representing the total order
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if thisRef or anotherStock are null
